  "text": "Kidson-Gerber and Gyamfi recommend asking the pregnant woman about unacceptable methods of treatment as soon as the first ambulatory visit, and documenting the answer [CITATION_1] . They advise consulting such patients in presence of the head of the department and, finally, giving them an authorised document or a magnetic card confirming refusal of blood transfusion; this makes patient identification much easier in ambulatory and hospital care setting [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] .",
